  "status": "Draft",
  "summary": "This standard is an extension of [ERC-721](./eip-721.md) that adds verifiable credential properties at the contract level. A verifiable credential is a secure digital certificate that encapsulates claims issued by a trusted authority and is designed to be tamper-evident and readily verifiable. It allows [ERC-721](./eip-721.md) tokens to natively reference and manage these credentials\u2014as well as other types of off-chain data\u2014by defining mechanisms for storage, encryption, revocation, and verification.",
  "title": "ERC-721 Verifiable Credential Extension"
}